cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CR 

The paper deals with person re-identification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a universal model learning approach, which involves training a deep model, making it relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper evaluates its proposed method on five standard benchmarks, which makes it relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
